Anchored Links are created differently in Divi 5 than Divi 4, but actually simple.
Anhor Link in menu item, process is the same as Divi 4:
  Open Menu
  Open Item to create link FROM
  Open Custom Link widget
  Use #CustomLink name (must be unique to this menu)
  Complete fields (basic)
Open Page in Divi 5 daashboard
Recommend opening the Layers panel on left column to identify specific Section, Row, or Module to insert CSS ID
Locate place where you desire the anchor
On left panel in Divi dashboard, selects:
  Advanced
  Attributes
  Add Attribute
  Attrtibute Name = "id"
  Attribute value must exactly match the name given from menu item = "CustonLink"
END 
